  <h1>Disconnect the Invoice Tool</h1>
  <p>To disconnect this tool from your QuickBooks Online account:</p>
  <ol style="text-align: left; max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto;">
    <li>Log in to QuickBooks Online.</li>
    <li>Go to <strong>Gear icon â†’ Apps</strong> (or My Apps).</li>
    <li>Find "Colorado Utility Finders Invoice Tool" (or the name you used).</li>
    <li>Click <strong>Disconnect</strong> or <strong>Remove</strong>.</li>
  </ol>
  <p>Once disconnected, the tool will no longer have access to your QBO data.</p>
